ances processes, allowing beneficiaries to challenge coverage decisions and ensuring timely resolution of disputes in compliance with federal timelines and standards.\n\nFurthermore, PDP Sponsors must exercise oversight over subcontractors and third-party administrators involved in plan operations, ensuring that all contracted entities also comply with 42 CFR Part 423. This includes monitoring subcontractor performance, enforcing contractual obligations, and maintaining accountability for any failures in compliance.\n\nIn summary, PDP Sponsors must fully comply with all aspects of 42 CFR Part 423, including enrollment, benefits, reporting, financial protections, quality assurance, appeals, payment rules, and subcontractor oversight. These requirements collectively ensure that Medicare Part D plans operate effectively, equitably, and in the best interest of beneficiaries, while maintaining regulatory compliance and financial stability.", "role": "assistant", "tool_calls": null, "function_call": null, "provider_specific_fields": {"refusal": null, "reasoning": null}}, "provider_specific_fields": {"stop_reason": null, "token_ids": null}}], "usage": {"completion_tokens": 449, "prompt_tokens": 246, "total_tokens": 695, "completion_tokens_details": null, "prompt_tokens_details": null}, "service_tier": null, "prompt_logprobs": null, "prompt_token_ids": null, "kv_transfer_params": null}}}